rule: Rule = "prospective" is marked as partially
Rule = "Partially" if "longitudinal" referred to
Rule = "baseline" not enough for search so marked as No
Rule = missing statistical model is Partially
Rule = Partially if describe some results but missing all numerical results of main statistical tests
Rule = if have intro is Yes
Rule = "Yes" if 1b_i is "Yes" because methods would have been fully described in abstract
Rule = partially have either recruitment details or states its from the UK Biobank but not both
Rule = "Yes" if state how "invited", or "NHS register"
Rule = "Partially" if say "general population"
Rule = "Partially" if state exposures were measured at baseline but don't give dates of baseline measurements
Rule = Yes if any follow-up date
Rule = NA if cross-sectional
Rule = "NA" because duplicate
Rule = Partially if don't give name of follow-up data source
Rule = "Yes" if define outcomes but missing ICD criteria
Rule = go with conservative estimate "Partially" because hard to resolve if other person looked less so would require extensive checking and debate
Rule = go with conservative estimate "Partially-External" because hard to resolve if other person looked less so would require extensive checking and debate
Rule = "NA" if subgroup analyses are the main analysis as this is covered by other items
Rule = NA if BMI because not a disease outcome
Rule = Partially-External if ICD-10 codes given but not ICD diagnostic criteria
Rule = "NA" for all studies because everyone had same assessment
Rule = "Partially" if missing statistical tests and don't say how interaction incoroporated into model
Rule = "Partially" if some missing data explained but not clearly for all variables
Rule = "NA" if include all eligible participants because no sampling strategy used
Rule = NA if no checks on robustness of results
Rule = "Yes" if give numbers in UKB, eligible and included
Rule = "NA" if complete case analysis
Rule = "Partially" if state excluded some variables because had missing data but don't indicate number of missing data for remaining variables
Rule = Yes if give any of mean/range/total
Rule = "Yes" if give number of outcome events, don't need rate too
Rule = "Partially" if make blanket statement about how covariates were chosen because associated with outcomes
Rule = "Partially" if missing Townsend quintile boundaries, but name other boundaries
Rule = "NA" if not a binary outcome
Rule = "NA" for case-controls
Rule = "Yes"if only p-value or significance indicated for interaction
Rule = "Yes" if give a numerical estimation of magnitude & direction for at least 1 source of bias
Rule = "Partially" if give non-numerical estimation of magnitude & or direction for at least 1 source of bias
Rule = "No" if do not give non-numerical estimation of magnitude or direction for any source of bias
Rule = Partially if make policy recommendations
Rule = "No" if make very strong causal statement or policy recommendation
